tory of knowledge and creativity, which it has preserved for all generations of Americans. We want to take advantage of this opportunity to energize national awareness of the critical role that all libraries play in keeping the spirit of creativity and free inquiry alive in our society.\"</p><p>Interpreting services (American Sign Language, Contact Signing, Oral and Tactile) will be provided if requested five business days in advance of the event. Call (202) 707-6362 TTY and voice to make a specific request or consult <a href=\"mailto:ADA@loc.gov\">ADA@loc.gov</a>. For other ADA accommodations please contact the Disability Employment Program Office at (202) 707-9948 TTY and (202) 707-7544 voice.</p>", "contact": "Craig D'Ooge (202) 707-9189", "contact_public": "(202) 707-5394", "media_advisory": "0", "press_release_number": "00-005", "profile": "news", "short_title": "Spring 2000 Literary Series"}, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington d.c."], "mime_type": ["text/html"], "online_format": ["web page"], "original_format": ["web page"], "other_title": [], "partof": ["news from the library of congress"], "shelf_id": "00-005", "subject": ["events"], "timestamp": "2020-12-12T16:21:48.092Z", "title": "Spring Literary Series Announced", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/prn-00-005/spring-literary-series-announced/2000-02-04/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["wordpress:/news/?p=35903", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-00-006/all-library-of-congress-buildings-closed-february-19-21/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-00-006/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-00-006/all-library-of-congress-buildings-closed-february-19-21/2000-01-31/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "2000-01-31", "dates": ["2000-01-31T00:00:00Z"], "description": ["<p>Beginning at 6 p.m. Friday, February 18, and continuing through Monday, February 21, all Library buildings will be closed. Because of the installation of a new telephone switch, there will be no operational telephones in any of th