nd multiracial states.</p><p>Sessions take place in the Library of Congress Coolidge Auditorium in the Jefferson Building March 7 and 8 from 9 a.m to 6:30 p.m. and in the Library's Mumford Room in the Madison Building on March 9 from 9 a.m. to 11:30 a.m. The symposium moves to the New York University School of Law's Vanderbilt Hall on March 10 from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m.</p><p>For a schedule of panels, participants, biographies, and abstracts, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/bicentennial\" title=\"Library of Congress' bicentennial website\" target=\"_blank\">www.loc.gov/bicentennial</a>.</p><p>In addition to support from the Library of Congress and the New York University School of Law, the symposium in funded in part through the generosity of Anthony and Beatrice Welters; William S. Hein &amp; Co.; Court Record Services, Inc.; and the Friends of the Law Library (in association with gifts from the Fannie Mae Foundation; O'Melveny &amp; Meyers LLP; the West Group; and LEXIS-NEXIS.)</p><p>Interpreting services (American Sign Language, Contact Signing, Oral and/or Tactile) will be provided if requested five business days in advance of the event. Call (202) 707-6362 TTY and voice to make a specific request. For other ADA accommodations please contact the Disability Employment Program Office at (202) 707-9948 TTY and (202) 707-7544 voice or <a href=\"mailto:ADA@loc.gov\">ADA@loc.gov</a>.</p>", "contact": "Craig D'Ooge (202) 707-9189", "contact_public": " Library of Congress: Rose Marie Clemandot (202) 707-5067; New York University: Joan Dim (212) 998-6849", "media_advisory": "0", "press_release_number": "00-004", "profile": "news", "short_title": "Symposium: Democracy and the Rule of Law", "sub_headline": "March 7-10 at the Library of Congress and New York University"}, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington d.c."], "mime_type": ["text/html"], "online_format": ["web page"], "original_format": ["web page"], "other_title": [], "partof": ["news from 