969ddca\">register here to participate</a>. Request ADA accommodations five business days in advance at 202-707-6362 or\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:ADA@loc.gov\">ADA@loc.gov</a>.</p><p>The Library of Congress is the world\u2019s largest library, offering access to the creative record of the United States \u2014 and extensive materials from around the world. It is the main research arm of the U.S. Congress and the home of the U.S. Copyright Office. Explore collections, reference services and other programs and plan a visit at <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov\">loc.gov</a>; access the official site for U.S. federal legislative information at <a href=\"http://www.congress.gov\">congress.gov</a>; and register creative works of authorship at <a href=\"http://www.copyright.gov\">copyright.gov</a>.</p>", "contact_press": "Kelley McNabb kmcnabb@loc.gov ", "contact_public": "Robert Brammer rbram@loc.gov", "contact_website": "[https://www.congress.gov|Congress.gov]", "division": ["crs"], "media_advisory": "0", "press_release_number": "20-052", "profile": "news", "short_title": "Library Hosts Public Forum on Congress.gov"}, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "washington d.c."], "mime_type": ["text/html"], "online_format": ["web page"], "original_format": ["web page"], "other_title": [], "partof": ["congressional research service", "news from the library of congress"], "shelf_id": "20-052", "subject": ["events"], "timestamp": "2020-12-12T16:22:42.913Z", "title": "Library Hosts Public Forum on Congress.gov Improvements and Priorities", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/prn-20-052/library-hosts-public-forum-on-congress-gov-improvements-and-priorities/2020-08-11/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["wordpress:/news/?p=40606", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-20-051/two-major-gifts-to-reimagine-visitor-experience-and-enhance-photography-collections-at-library-of-congress/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-20-051/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/prn-20-051/two-major-gifts-to-reima